This article is a press release from the White House announcing Executive Order 13552, which amends the Manual for Courts-Martial in the United States. The order states that Parts II and IV of the Manual are amended as described in the attached Annex. The amendments will take effect 30 days from the date of the order. It also clarifies that the amendments will not apply retroactively and will not invalidate any ongoing legal proceedings or actions initiated before the effective date of the order. The press release is signed by President Barack Obama and dated August 31, 2010.